---
import FridayHarborLayout from '../../layouts/FridayHarborLayout.astro';
import { entries } from '../../data/friday-harbor';
const entry = entries.find(e => e.slug === '2026-04-29-when-the-model-draws-seattle')!;
---
<FridayHarborLayout entry={entry}>
  <figure slot="figure" class="seamap-figure">
    <div class="seamap-pair">
      <div class="seamap-panel">
        <div class="seamap-tag">
          <span data-lang="en">As the city publishes it</span>
          <span data-lang="zh">城市公布的版本</span>
        </div>
        <div class="seamap-stage" id="stage-real" data-source="real" aria-label="Seattle neighborhoods, City of Seattle GIS">
          <p class="map-status"><span data-lang="en">Loading map…</span><span data-lang="zh">地图加载中…</span></p>
        </div>
        <p class="seamap-source">
          <span data-lang="en">Source: City of Seattle Neighborhood Map Atlas (90 named neighborhoods)</span>
          <span data-lang="zh">数据：西雅图市政府《Neighborhood Map Atlas》（共 90 个标准命名街区）</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seamap-panel">
        <div class="seamap-tag tag-claude">
          <span data-lang="en">As Claude draws it from memory</span>
          <span data-lang="zh">Claude 凭印象画出的版本</span>
        </div>
        <div class="seamap-stage" id="stage-claude" data-source="claude" aria-label="Seattle neighborhoods, AI from memory">
          <p class="map-status"><span data-lang="en">Loading map…</span><span data-lang="zh">地图加载中…</span></p>
        </div>
        <p class="seamap-source">
          <span data-lang="en">Source: Claude (claude-opus-4-7) asked for GeoJSON polygons of named Seattle neighborhoods, no map allowed.</span>
          <span data-lang="zh">数据：Claude（claude-opus-4-7）被请求按记忆给出西雅图街区 GeoJSON 多边形，未查询任何地图。</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <figcaption data-lang="en">
      <b>The city has 90 named neighborhoods. Asked to draw them from memory, Claude returned 35 axis-aligned rectangles — and forgot the rest.</b>
      The two maps above use the same projection, the same scale, and the same labels. The left panel is what the City of Seattle GIS office publishes. The right panel is what the model holds — boundaries that snap to lat/lon grid lines, blocks of city that the model has condensed into a single name, and parts of South Seattle that quietly fall off the page.
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-real"></span>
        <span><b>Sage</b> — neighborhood polygons as the city publishes them. Edges follow streets, water, and topography.</span>
      </span>
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-claude"></span>
        <span><b>Terracotta</b> — what Claude returned. Edges are straight lines between rounded coordinates because the model does not really have a coastline; it has a list.</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <figcaption data-lang="zh">
      <b>这座城市有 90 个标准命名街区。当被要求凭记忆画出来时，Claude 给出了 35 个轴向对齐的矩形——其余的，它没记起来。</b>
      上面两张图共享同一个投影、同一个比例尺、同一组标签。左图是西雅图市 GIS 办公室公布的版本。右图是这个语言模型大脑里的版本——边界对齐在经纬度网格上，几个邻近街区被模型合并成一个名字，南西雅图的某些区域，干脆从纸面上掉下去了。
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-real"></span>
        <span><b>鼠尾草色</b>—— 市政府公布的街区多边形。边界沿街道、水岸与地形走。</span>
      </span>
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-claude"></span>
        <span><b>赭红色</b>—— Claude 返回的多边形。边界是取整经纬度之间的直线段——因为模型并没有海岸线，它只有一份列表。</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <aside class="seamap-stats" aria-label="key comparison figures">
      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">90</span>
        <span class="stat-label">neighborhoods in the city's official atlas</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">90</span>
        <span class="stat-label">市政府官方街区图册中的街区数</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">35</span>
        <span class="stat-label">neighborhoods Claude was able to name and draw</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">35</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Claude 能叫出名字并画出位置的街区数</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">100<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">of Claude's polygons are axis-aligned rectangles</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">100<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">Claude 的多边形——全部都是与经纬度对齐的矩形</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 800<small>&nbsp;m</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">median centroid drift from the real boundary</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 800<small>&nbsp;m</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">质心相对真实边界的中位偏移</span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </figure>

  <div slot="notebook-en">
    <p>
      The exercise on this page is small. Take the City of Seattle's official
      list of named neighborhoods. Ask a state-of-the-art language model — in
      this case Claude (Opus 4.7) — to return GeoJSON polygons for them. Tell
      the model not to look anything up. Render both layers at the same scale,
      with the same projection, on the same page. Look at what comes back.
    </p>
    <p>
      The answer is on the right. Claude returned thirty-five polygons. Every
      single one is a rectangle whose sides are aligned to lines of latitude
      and longitude. The corners sit on coordinates rounded to three decimal
      places. The model did not draw a city; it drew a checklist with bounding
      boxes attached. Lake Washington, Puget Sound, Lake Union, the
      Lake Washington Ship Canal, the Duwamish — none of these are present in
      what came back, because none of them are in the prompt and the model
      does not have a way to reach for them on its own.
    </p>
    <p>
      The neighborhoods that <em>did</em> come back are also instructive.
      The model returned Capitol Hill, Ballard, Fremont, Wallingford,
      Queen Anne, Magnolia, the U District — neighborhoods that are talked
      about, written about, real-estate-listed, marketed, gentrified, sung
      about. It returned roughly four neighborhoods inside Rainier Valley
      where the city has fourteen — Hillman City, Brighton, Dunlap, Rainier
      Beach, Lakewood, Genesee, all collapsed into "Rainier Valley." It did
      not return Yesler Terrace, Atlantic, Holly Park, High Point, Riverview,
      Roxhill, Westwood, Pinehurst, Olympic Hills, Bitter Lake, Haller Lake,
      Cedar Park, Matthews Beach. The pattern of what is named and what is
      forgotten is not random. It tracks who writes about Seattle on the
      internet, in English, in volume.
    </p>
    <p>
      A second pattern: the polygons that did come back have rounded edges.
      The model knows Capitol Hill is "around 47.62 north, 122.32 west." It
      does not know that Capitol Hill's western edge is the I-5 trench. It
      does not know that its southern edge follows East Madison and East
      Pike, which are diagonal streets that no axis-aligned rectangle can
      capture. The model's geometry is the geometry of memorized centroids
      with arbitrary rectangular skirts thrown over them. The actual city is
      drawn by streets and water, neither of which the model is consulting.
    </p>
    <p>
      So this map is a small anti-map of the kind GIS Friday Harbor entries
      argue for: it shows what is missing more than what is there. The model
      is good at many things. It is not good at being a map of Seattle. The
      reason is not that it lacks intelligence — it is that what it has read
      about Seattle is not the same as what Seattle is.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div slot="notebook-zh">
    <p>
      这一页做的事情很简单：拿西雅图市政府公布的标准街区列表，请目前最新的语言模型——这里用的是
      Claude（Opus 4.7）——返回每个街区的 GeoJSON 多边形。要求它不要查阅任何资料。把两层数据用同一个投影、同一个比例、放在同一个页面上一起渲染。然后看返回了什么。
    </p>
    <p>
      右边那张图，就是答案。Claude 返回了 35 个多边形。每一个，都是一组与经纬线对齐的矩形。所有顶点都落在保留三位小数的坐标上。这不是一个城市的地图；这是一份"清单 + 外接矩形"。华盛顿湖、普吉特海湾、联合湖、华盛顿湖船运河、Duwamish 河——这些全都不在它返回的内容里，因为它们也不在 prompt 里；模型没有办法主动伸手去拿它们。
    </p>
    <p>
      返回的那些街区，也是有规律的。Capitol Hill、Ballard、Fremont、Wallingford、
      Queen Anne、Magnolia、U District——这些是人们会聊、会写、会挂房产中介牌、会被士绅化、会出现在歌词里的街区。它在 Rainier Valley 里返回了大约 4 个子街区，而市政府那里有 14 个——Hillman City、Brighton、Dunlap、Rainier Beach、Lakewood、Genesee 等等，全部被它合并成了一个"Rainier Valley"。它完全没有返回的：Yesler Terrace、Atlantic、Holly Park、High Point、Riverview、Roxhill、Westwood、Pinehurst、Olympic Hills、Bitter Lake、Haller Lake、Cedar Park、Matthews Beach。被叫得出名字的与被遗忘的，不是随机的——它跟踪的是「谁在用英文，在互联网上，大量地写过西雅图」。
    </p>
    <p>
      第二个规律：被画出来的那些街区，边界是圆滑取整后的。模型知道 Capitol Hill 大约在 47.62°N, 122.32°W。它不知道 Capitol Hill 的西界是 I-5 高速路下沉段。它不知道南界其实是沿着 E Madison 和 E Pike 这两条斜街——任何与经纬度对齐的矩形都无法表示这种斜线。模型的几何，是「被记住的中心点 + 任意大小的外接矩形」的几何。真实城市的几何，是由街道与水岸刻出的；这两样东西，模型都没在查。
    </p>
    <p>
      所以这张图是一种 GIS Friday Harbor 那一脉所主张的「反图」（anti-map）——它要展示的是缺席本身，而不是在场。这不是说模型不聪明。它只是不擅长当一张西雅图的地图。原因也不复杂：它读到的关于西雅图的东西，并不等于西雅图。
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul slot="provenance-en">
    <li>Real boundaries: City of Seattle Neighborhood Map Atlas via the <a href="https://github.com/seattleio/seattle-boundaries-data" rel="noopener">seattleio/seattle-boundaries-data</a> repository, filtered to <code>city == "Seattle"</code>; coordinates rounded to 4 decimal places (~11 m precision).</li>
    <li>AI boundaries: prompt issued to Claude Opus 4.7 within this writing session, asking for GeoJSON polygons of named Seattle neighborhoods with no external lookups. The returned polygons are stored verbatim — not reshaped, not cleaned. The model's output is the data.</li>
    <li>Both layers projected with d3-geo's Albers projection, parallels at 47.5° and 47.75°, centred on Seattle.</li>
    <li>Centroid drift figure computed locally as the median Haversine distance between the centroid of each Claude polygon and the centroid of the same-named real polygon (35 pairs).</li>
    <li>Source map &amp; build script: <code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-29-when-the-model-draws-seattle.astro</code>; data files in <code>public/data/seattle-neighborhoods-real.geojson</code> and <code>seattle-neighborhoods-claude.geojson</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <ul slot="provenance-zh">
    <li>真实边界：西雅图市《Neighborhood Map Atlas》，经 <a href="https://github.com/seattleio/seattle-boundaries-data" rel="noopener">seattleio/seattle-boundaries-data</a> 仓库加载，筛选 <code>city == "Seattle"</code>；坐标保留 4 位小数（约 11 m 精度）。</li>
    <li>AI 边界：在本次写作会话中，向 Claude Opus 4.7 发出请求，要求返回西雅图街区的 GeoJSON 多边形，禁止查阅外部资料。返回的多边形原样保存——未做任何整形、对齐或清洗。模型输出本身就是数据。</li>
    <li>两层数据均用 d3-geo 的 Albers 投影渲染，标准纬线 47.5°、47.75°，中心点设在西雅图。</li>
    <li>质心偏移：本地计算，每对同名街区（共 35 对）的多边形质心间的 Haversine 距离，取其中位数。</li>
    <li>源码与构建脚本：<code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-29-when-the-model-draws-seattle.astro</code>；数据文件：<code>public/data/seattle-neighborhoods-real.geojson</code> 与 <code>seattle-neighborhoods-claude.geojson</code>。</li>
  </ul>
</FridayHarborLayout>

<style>
